  "title": "七面钟之谜",
  "source_file": "data\\raw\\detectiveqa\\novel_data_en\\144-七面钟之谜-阿加莎克里斯蒂.txt",
  "chunk_index": 3,
  "summary": "Rupert Bettman, referred to by the group as the \"Chimpanzee,\" executes the prank by carefully placing eight of Mr. Dumplin's alarm clocks near Gerry Wade's bed to ensure they ring loudly without waking him. When the alarms go off at dawn, the noise is deafening, yet Gerry remains asleep. Ronnie DeVille is startled by the sound, but Gerry's lack of reaction leads the conspirators to speculate that he is either playing a trick on them or suffers from a medical issue, such as damaged eardrums.\n\nBy noon, the group is disappointed that Gerry has not appeared. The butler, Mr. Truddwell, informs them that Williams went to check on Gerry and found that he had \"slept through.\" Truddwell reveals that he has already locked Gerry's door, summoned Dr. Carruthers, and intends to notify Sir Oswald. Ronnie is visibly shaken, and Jimmy Sycamore attempts to console him on a terrace, privately wondering if the prank has turned into a murder.\n\nDr. Carruthers informs Ronnie and Jimmy that Gerry died from an overdose of chloral hydrate, noting a bottle and cup near the bed. While the doctor suggests the death might be a suicide, Ronnie firmly denies that Gerry would do such a thing. The doctor inquires about potential motives involving money or women, but Ronnie denies any such troubles. Upon learning that Gerry has a half-sister living at Dean Abbey, Ronnie volunteers to notify her and asks Jimmy to drive him there.",
